Personal Portfolio Project
Welcome to my personal portfolio project! This project is a fully responsive personal portfolio website built using HTML and CSS. It showcases various sections that provide information about me, my future goals, my skills, and a way to get in touch. Below, you will find a detailed description of each section included in the portfolio.

Sections
About Me
In the "About Me" section, I introduce myself and provide a brief overview of my background, interests, and experiences. This section helps visitors get to know who I am and what drives me.

Future Goals
The "Future Goals" section outlines my aspirations and objectives for the future. Here, I discuss my career ambitions, personal development plans, and the milestones I aim to achieve in the coming years.

Skills
In the "Skills" section, I highlight my technical and soft skills. This includes a detailed list of programming languages, tools, frameworks, and other proficiencies that I have acquired. It gives a clear picture of what I bring to the table professionally.

Contact Us
The "Contact Us" section provides a simple and effective way for visitors to get in touch with me. It includes a contact form where users can send me messages directly. Additionally, my social media links and email address are provided for further contact options.

Features
Responsive Design: The portfolio is designed to be fully responsive, ensuring a seamless experience across various devices and screen sizes.
Clean and Modern Layout: The website features a clean and modern design, making it easy to navigate and visually appealing.
Interactive Elements: Interactive elements such as hover effects and smooth scrolling enhance the user experience.
Technologies Used
HTML: Structure and content of the website.
CSS: Styling and layout of the website.
Feel free to explore the different sections of my portfolio to learn more about me and my work. Thank you for visiting!

This project represents my journey and growth as a web developer, and I am excited to share it with you. If you have any feedback or questions, please do not hesitate to reach out through the contact section.

